headline: What the F-150 Lightning Plant Shutdown Means for Ford Stock’s 2025 Valuation
summary: Deciding what to do with Ford Motor stock right now is trickier than it might seem at first glance. If you thought this old-school automaker was all about slow and steady, think again. Over the past year, Ford has quietly surged, racking up a 14.6% gain, with a remarkable 93.8% return over the last five years. Still, there’s been turbulence. This past week alone, shares dropped nearly 10%, largely in response to a fire at a key supplier’s aluminum plant, throwing a wrench into F-150 Lightning...
